# Adapters

Define adapters to implement third-party libraries in order to centralize functionality in a single place and avoid repeating the same code across the codebase.

Adapters also make it easier to:
- Replace libraries in the future
- Improve testability
- Maintain consistency across the application

Adapters can be implemented in different ways:
- Exported variables
- Exported objects with functions
- Static classes

- Always use adapters instead of directly importing third-party libraries
- Keep adapters small and focused
- Avoid business logic inside adapters
- Adapters should only wrap external libraries
- Place adapters inside the infrastructure/adapters directory

## Environment Adapter

